New Sonic 3 Game Card Regent, Sega Genesis sold separately.

00:03:04.860 --> 00:03:08.860
Nick, Nick, Nick, Nick, Nick, Nick, Nick...

00:03:08.860 --> 00:03:20.300
A Snicket.

00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:22.300
Snicks there. Snicks here.

00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:23.300
It's sneaking out.

00:03:23.300 --> 00:03:25.300
Saturday night, Nickelodeon.

00:03:25.300 --> 00:03:26.300
It's sick.

00:03:26.300 --> 00:03:26.800
Snick!

00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:27.800
And you can snick.

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:29.800
It's time to snick.

00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:30.800
Now!

00:03:30.800 --> 00:03:38.120
I don't know exactly when it happened, but it seems like one day I woke up and I had an opinion about everything.

00:03:38.120 --> 00:03:44.120
Like what flavor ice cream goes with double fudge almond nut cake and exactly how loud to play the new nine-inch nail song.

00:03:44.120 --> 00:03:47.620
Not to mention how much money the U.S. ought to give Boris Yeltsin.

00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:52.120
So I've been thinking about how cool it would be to be a professional opinion giver.

00:03:52.120 --> 00:03:54.620
First, I thought I could be a fortune teller.

00:03:54.620 --> 00:03:57.120
What do you see, Madam Clarissa?

00:03:57.120 --> 00:04:04.620
You have a husband named Marshall, a son named Ferguson, and you work in the Children's Museum.

00:04:04.620 --> 00:04:05.620
Any other questions?

00:04:05.620 --> 00:04:06.620
Yeah.

00:04:06.620 --> 00:04:10.380
Can I have my money back?

00:04:10.380 --> 00:04:13.880
Then I thought being a famous guru would be interesting.

00:04:13.880 --> 00:04:18.180
What can you tell me?

00:04:18.180 --> 00:04:19.680
Oh, I was one.

00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:23.680
Today is the first day of the rest of your life.

00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:25.180
Is that all?

00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:29.070
And you look better in blue.

00:04:29.070 --> 00:04:33.570
Of course, if I were a bartender, I could give advice that was a little more down-to-earth.

00:04:33.570 --> 00:04:35.570
And then she left me.

00:04:35.570 --> 00:04:38.570
She just waltzed out the door.

00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:39.570
No goodbye.

00:04:39.570 --> 00:04:41.570
No nothing.

00:04:41.570 --> 00:04:43.570
What'll I do?

00:04:43.570 --> 00:04:50.300
Well, you might try paying your tab and then how about going home?

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:54.300
But then I had a surefire way to get my opinions out there.

00:04:54.300 --> 00:04:55.300
An advice column.

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:58.300
Right where everyone can see it in the Thomas Tupper Time.

00:04:58.300 --> 00:05:00.800
Hey, on the editor, right?

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:02.800
Now all I need is a pen name.

00:05:02.800 --> 00:05:07.800
I've always liked the name Alice, as in Alice B. Tuckless literary sidekick.

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:08.800
That's it!

00:05:08.800 --> 00:05:10.800
And Landers move over.

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:12.800
Alice B. Talking has arrived.

00:05:12.800 --> 00:06:08.590
I introduced Alice B. Talking to the Thomas Tupper Times readership.

00:06:08.590 --> 00:06:10.090
The response has been great.

00:06:10.090 --> 00:06:12.090
A little on the silly side, but hey.

00:06:12.090 --> 00:06:20.970
Hey, Alice.

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:22.970
Sam, my name's Clarissa.

00:06:22.970 --> 00:06:24.970
You could have fooled me, Alice, but you didn't.

00:06:24.970 --> 00:06:25.970
Okay.

00:06:25.970 --> 00:06:26.970
How'd you guess?

00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:28.970
Clarissa, I know your style.

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:31.970
Who else would actually answer a letter from a guy who thinks he's a vampire?

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:33.970
Yeah, that was a good one.

00:06:33.970 --> 00:06:37.970
Dear Mr. Dracula, have you ever considered becoming a vegetarian?

00:06:37.970 --> 00:06:41.970
I hear they have a soybean blood substitute that's just as tasty as the real thing.

00:06:41.970 --> 00:06:42.970
Pretty funny, Clarissa.

00:06:42.970 --> 00:06:43.970
Thanks.

00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:45.970
This column is the biggest thing at Thomas Tupper.

00:06:45.970 --> 00:06:47.970
Everybody's talking about it.

00:06:47.970 --> 00:06:49.970
Well, giving people advice is really fun.

00:06:49.970 --> 00:06:53.970
Yeah, the last person I gave advice to just won the Ditzberger Prize for sportswriting.

00:06:53.970 --> 00:06:55.970
Your dad? Really? That's great!

00:06:55.970 --> 00:06:58.970
Yeah, he was gonna write about the Rhode Island Tiddlywinks Championships,

00:06:58.970 --> 00:07:01.970
but I convinced him that the Super Bowl might have a wider appeal.

00:07:01.970 --> 00:07:04.970
Good thinking, Sam. I'll call you if I need anything.

00:07:04.970 --> 00:07:06.970
Anytime. See you later.

00:07:06.970 --> 00:07:07.970
Alice.

00:07:07.970 --> 00:07:08.970
Bye, Sam.

00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:12.790
Now, where was I?

00:07:12.790 --> 00:07:19.960
Dear Alice, my boyfriend wants me to get a nose ring made of stainless steel,

00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:21.960
but I want one of tempered brass.

00:07:21.960 --> 00:07:23.960
What should I do?

00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:26.960
Well, that's a deeply philosophical question if ever I heard one.

00:07:26.960 --> 00:07:28.960
Boy, I love this job.

00:07:28.960 --> 00:07:33.460
Now, I personally don't see anything wrong with either one of these.

00:07:33.460 --> 00:07:35.460
They're very imaginative, Marshal.

00:07:35.460 --> 00:07:37.460
Then why won't she accept any of my designs?

00:07:37.460 --> 00:07:40.460
Well, maybe what Mrs. Fartle was with the Adopt-a-Pet Center

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:42.460
is something more practical.

00:07:42.460 --> 00:07:44.460
They all are practical.

00:07:44.460 --> 00:07:46.460
Now, look at this.

00:07:46.460 --> 00:07:50.460
Every time somebody adopts a pet, the tail wax.

00:07:50.460 --> 00:07:53.460
I don't know about that. Yeah, that's pretty public.

00:07:53.460 --> 00:07:55.460
I love that, Dad. It's great.

00:07:55.460 --> 00:07:57.460
Yeah, well, I wish Mrs. Fartle didn't,

00:07:57.460 --> 00:07:59.460
and maybe I'd get a decent night's sleep for a change.

00:07:59.460 --> 00:08:02.460
Marshal, honey, I feel bad that I hooked you up with this thing.

00:08:02.460 --> 00:08:04.460
I mean, you were nice enough to do the work for nothing after all.

00:08:04.460 --> 00:08:05.460
What?

00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:07.460
Well, I want to contribute, but I got to tell you,

00:08:07.460 --> 00:08:09.460
sometimes I get the feeling the only thing that I'm really doing

00:08:09.460 --> 00:08:11.460
is stroking Mrs. Fartle's oversized ego.

00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:13.460
Did you say for nothing?

00:08:13.460 --> 00:08:15.460
For the new Adopt-a-Pet Center, Ferguson.

00:08:15.460 --> 00:08:16.460
Yeah, so?

00:08:16.460 --> 00:08:18.460
So, you know, they're a little low on funds.

00:08:18.460 --> 00:08:20.460
I'm doing this work pro bono.

00:08:20.460 --> 00:08:22.460
Pro bono?

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:25.460
You mean as opposed to share bono?

00:08:25.460 --> 00:08:27.460
Get it? Share bono? Pro bono?

00:08:27.460 --> 00:08:29.460
Pro bono means for free, Ferguson.

00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:32.460
And her name isn't share bono, it's share.

00:08:32.460 --> 00:08:34.460
Uh-huh, so let me get this straight.

00:08:34.460 --> 00:08:35.460
You do the work.

00:08:35.460 --> 00:08:36.460
That's right.

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:37.460
And you don't get paid?

00:08:37.460 --> 00:08:39.460
Well, there are compensations other than money, Ferguson.

00:08:39.460 --> 00:08:40.460
Really?

00:08:40.460 --> 00:08:41.460
Oh, like what?

00:08:41.460 --> 00:08:43.460
Oh, you know, like the good feeling you get

00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:46.460
when you do some work for a worthy cause.

00:08:46.460 --> 00:08:48.460
But you still don't get paid.

00:08:48.460 --> 00:08:50.460
You know, that's the point, Ferguson.

00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:54.260
Now, you know, I'm going to explain this later.

00:08:54.260 --> 00:08:57.260
My son is charitably challenged.

00:08:57.260 --> 00:08:59.260
I'm going back to the salt mines.

00:08:59.260 --> 00:09:00.260
Good luck, Marshall.

00:09:00.260 --> 00:09:02.260
I'll make you some extra strong ginseng tea

00:09:02.260 --> 00:09:03.260
and bring it in.

00:09:03.260 --> 00:09:04.260
Thanks.

00:09:04.260 --> 00:09:05.260
Come on, boy.

00:09:05.260 --> 00:09:10.360
Pretty funny line, huh?

00:09:10.360 --> 00:09:12.360
Pro bono? Share bono? Yeah?

00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:14.360
I'm laughing on the inside.

00:09:14.360 --> 00:09:16.360
You thought it was amusing, Ferguson?

00:09:16.360 --> 00:09:17.360
Thanks, Mom.

00:09:17.360 --> 00:09:20.360
When I'm rich and famous and I have my own TV series,

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:23.360
I won't forget those that stood behind me

00:09:23.360 --> 00:09:26.360
in my lean years and those that didn't.

00:09:26.360 --> 00:09:27.360
Your own TV series?

00:09:27.360 --> 00:09:30.360
You mean besides America's least wanted?

00:09:30.360 --> 00:09:32.360
Pretty funny, sis.

00:09:32.360 --> 00:09:34.360
But not funny enough for the big time, I'm afraid.

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:36.360
At least not funny enough for my show.

00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:37.360
What show, Ferguson?

00:09:37.360 --> 00:09:39.360
The TV show that I'm going to star in

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:41.360
once I make my mark as a stand-up comic.

00:09:41.360 --> 00:09:43.360
If I had my own show,

00:09:43.360 --> 00:09:45.360
do you have any idea what I'd make?

00:09:45.360 --> 00:09:48.360
Yeah, a lot of people sick.

00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:51.360
You know, we comics call people like you, sis.

00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:52.360
Okay, I'll bite.

00:09:52.360 --> 00:09:54.360
Material.

00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:57.180
I'll get it.

00:09:57.180 --> 00:10:03.220
Yes, this is Clarissa.

00:10:03.220 --> 00:10:05.220
Yes, I am the editor of.

00:10:05.220 --> 00:10:08.220
Oh, you mean our advice column, Alice B?

00:10:08.220 --> 00:10:10.220
Well, sure I know who writes it.

00:10:10.220 --> 00:10:12.220
Oh, sorry, but I can't.

00:10:12.220 --> 00:10:16.560
You're Wally Kelp from Groove Magazine.

00:10:16.560 --> 00:10:18.560
Of course I've heard of you.

00:10:18.560 --> 00:10:21.560
Well, actually, I write it.

00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:24.560
Yeah, well, it's sort of a secret, but uh...

00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:25.560
Tomorrow?

00:10:25.560 --> 00:10:33.580
Sure, why not?

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:35.580
It's a boy genius editor of the magazine called Groove,

00:10:35.580 --> 00:10:38.580
and he wants to run my advice column in his magazine.

00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:40.580
Wow, that's impressive.

00:10:40.580 --> 00:10:42.580
Mom, Groove Magazine is really out there.

00:10:42.580 --> 00:10:43.580
It's one of my favorite zines.

00:10:43.580 --> 00:10:45.580
Well, congratulations, Clarissa.

00:10:45.580 --> 00:10:47.580
I'm sure you will do a terrific job.

00:10:47.580 --> 00:10:48.580
Thanks, Mom.

00:10:48.580 --> 00:10:51.580
I better get this gensing tea into your father.

00:10:51.580 --> 00:10:56.520
Alice B talking?

00:10:56.520 --> 00:10:58.520
In the pages of Groove Magazine?

00:10:58.520 --> 00:10:59.520
Hmm.

00:10:59.520 --> 00:11:02.520
Doing this column might turn out to be the best advice I ever gave myself.

00:11:02.520 --> 00:11:07.250
I can't believe I know some D-Wrights for Groove Magazine.

00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:08.250
This is so cool.

00:11:08.250 --> 00:11:10.250
Let's hope so, Sam.

00:11:10.250 --> 00:11:12.250
Hey, here it is.

00:11:12.250 --> 00:11:15.250
Dumb boyfriends, stupid teachers, bad hair day.

00:11:15.250 --> 00:11:17.250
Right me, I'm Alice and you're not.

00:11:17.250 --> 00:11:19.250
But this ad should get lots of great letters.

00:11:19.250 --> 00:11:23.250
Listen to what I wrote that girl from Thomas Tupper who had the nose ring question.

00:11:23.250 --> 00:11:26.250
How'd you get permission to run the Thomas Tupper letters in Groove anyway?

00:11:26.250 --> 00:11:28.250
Oh, I know the editor.

00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:32.250
Dear Steele or Brass, why can something as boring as a little nose ring?

00:11:32.250 --> 00:11:35.250
I suggest you weld a huge block of cement to the side of your head.

00:11:35.250 --> 00:11:39.250
Or if you're not into concrete, how about tattooing your phone number across your forehead?

00:11:39.250 --> 00:11:41.250
That way your boyfriend won't forget to call you.

00:11:41.250 --> 00:11:43.250
Yours, Alice.

00:11:43.250 --> 00:11:44.250
I don't know, Clarissa.

00:11:44.250 --> 00:11:47.250
What if she does get a tattoo in the middle of her forehead?

00:11:47.250 --> 00:11:49.250
I'm just joking around, Sam.

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:52.250
Besides, who'd be crazy enough to take this stuff seriously anyway?

00:11:52.250 --> 00:11:53.250
You never know.

00:11:53.250 --> 00:12:02.340
Hey, are you Alice B talking?

00:12:02.340 --> 00:12:03.340
Yeah.

00:12:03.340 --> 00:12:04.340
Cool.

00:12:04.340 --> 00:12:06.340
Delivery from Groove Magazine.

00:12:06.340 --> 00:12:08.340
Great, Sam, these must be the letters.

00:12:08.340 --> 00:12:09.340
I hope I got enough.

00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:11.340
Whoa, wait, there's more.

00:12:11.340 --> 00:12:12.340
Oh, bring them in.

00:12:12.340 --> 00:12:47.250
Gee, I guess Alice B talking is popular already.

00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:51.190
Listen to this.

00:12:51.190 --> 00:12:56.190
Dear Alice, I dreamt I was an aunt and now I can't stay away from picnics.

00:12:56.190 --> 00:12:57.190
What should I do?

00:12:57.190 --> 00:12:59.190
Signed, looking for leftovers.

00:12:59.190 --> 00:13:00.190
Here's one.

00:13:00.190 --> 00:13:03.190
Dear Alice, when my head itches, my butt sweats.

00:13:03.190 --> 00:13:04.190
Does this mean I'm a genius?

00:13:04.190 --> 00:13:06.190
So I'm baffled in Boston.

00:13:06.190 --> 00:13:08.190
Who said there's no such thing as a stupid question?

00:13:08.190 --> 00:13:11.190
Hey kid, how's everybody doing tonight?

00:13:11.190 --> 00:13:15.190
Oh, look, my sister's become a bag person.

00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:16.190
Get it?

00:13:16.190 --> 00:13:17.190
Bag?

00:13:17.190 --> 00:13:18.190
Person?

00:13:18.190 --> 00:13:19.190
Yeah, I get it.

00:13:19.190 --> 00:13:20.190
Was that funny?

00:13:20.190 --> 00:13:21.190
What's a matter?

00:13:21.190 --> 00:13:24.190
You look like a sad sack.

00:13:24.190 --> 00:13:25.190
Get it?

00:13:25.190 --> 00:13:26.190
Sad sack?

00:13:26.190 --> 00:13:27.190
We get it.

00:13:27.190 --> 00:13:29.190
Whoa, the original good humor, man.

00:13:29.190 --> 00:13:33.190
I'm just chopping up my improv skills for the talent night next week.

00:13:33.190 --> 00:13:37.190
You see, I'm sending out headshots to every TV producer on the coast.

00:13:37.190 --> 00:13:40.190
I'm sure they'll be flying in for the show, Ferg.

00:13:40.190 --> 00:13:44.190
And boy, will their arms be tired.

00:13:44.190 --> 00:13:46.190
How can this guy be so darn funny?

00:13:46.190 --> 00:13:55.740
One word, Sam.

00:13:55.740 --> 00:13:58.980
Timing.

00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:05.290
Speaking of which, I think it's time for Alice to get down to business.

00:14:05.290 --> 00:14:07.290
Okay, it's almost midnight.

00:14:07.290 --> 00:14:11.290
I spent all day reading these letters and sorting them into piles.

00:14:11.290 --> 00:14:14.290
Broken heart.

00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:17.290
Hymnful problem.

00:14:17.290 --> 00:14:19.290
Family feuds.

00:14:19.290 --> 00:14:21.290
Weird.

00:14:21.290 --> 00:14:22.290
And too weird.

00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:39.360
Let's see where this one goes.

00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:43.360
Dear Alice, I'm the one who wrote you before about the nose ring, remember?

00:14:43.360 --> 00:14:47.360
Well, I took your advice and got a tattoo.

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:50.360
It's not in my forehead, but it's bad enough.

00:14:50.360 --> 00:14:53.360
