01:50:06.940 --> 01:50:09.940
I intend to use that ring for myself.

01:50:09.940 --> 01:50:11.940
Now give it to me!

01:50:11.940 --> 01:50:13.940
I wouldn't, if I were you, professor.

01:50:13.940 --> 01:50:17.940
That odor you smell is kerosene.

01:50:17.940 --> 01:50:21.940
I've soaked most of these crates one touch of this torch,

01:50:21.940 --> 01:50:24.940
and this museum becomes a furnace.

01:50:24.940 --> 01:50:28.940
You wouldn't want to take that risk.

01:50:28.940 --> 01:50:31.940
I say we give it to him.

01:50:31.940 --> 01:50:32.940
I have to think.

01:50:32.940 --> 01:50:34.940
There's nothing to think about.

01:50:34.940 --> 01:50:35.940
We've got to do it.

01:50:35.940 --> 01:50:37.940
Josh, give him the ring.

01:50:37.940 --> 01:50:38.940
What about?

01:50:38.940 --> 01:50:40.940
Just give him the ring, understand?

01:50:40.940 --> 01:50:46.340
Good boy.

01:50:46.340 --> 01:50:49.340
Now, slide it over here.

01:50:49.340 --> 01:50:53.450
Come on, come on.

01:50:53.450 --> 01:50:57.950
Let them go.

01:50:57.950 --> 01:51:00.950
I'm afraid I can't do that, professor.

01:51:00.950 --> 01:51:03.950
I'm sure you'd go right to the authorities.

01:51:03.950 --> 01:51:06.950
I can't have them track me for the rest of eternity now.

01:51:06.950 --> 01:51:07.950
Can I?

01:51:07.950 --> 01:51:08.950
Don't do it, doctor, please.

01:51:08.950 --> 01:51:11.950
At least let us see if the ring works.

01:51:11.950 --> 01:51:43.620
Why not?

01:51:43.620 --> 01:51:49.620
Behold, you are now gazing at an immortal.

01:51:49.620 --> 01:51:55.990
What's this?

01:51:55.990 --> 01:52:02.370
You can't move.

01:52:02.370 --> 01:52:16.180
Save and a beauty.

01:52:16.180 --> 01:52:25.630
Incredible.

01:52:25.630 --> 01:52:33.120
I guess he got what he wanted after all.

01:52:33.120 --> 01:52:34.120
Immortality.

01:52:34.120 --> 01:52:36.120
Very clever, little sister.

01:52:36.120 --> 01:52:38.120
Excuse me?

01:52:38.120 --> 01:52:41.120
The translations, as I said, the ring brings eternity.

01:52:41.120 --> 01:52:43.120
The elixir brings life.

01:52:43.120 --> 01:52:46.120
He knew he had the ring, but he didn't know he had this.

01:52:46.120 --> 01:52:58.210
The elixir? It's real.

01:52:58.210 --> 01:53:03.210
Um, we forgot to tell you, Dad, the mummy's missing.

01:53:03.210 --> 01:53:09.280
What? My God, it's alive.

01:53:09.280 --> 01:53:19.820
It sure brings life.

01:53:19.820 --> 01:53:21.820
The ring brings eternity.

01:53:21.820 --> 01:53:25.220
I don't!

01:53:25.220 --> 01:54:27.250
She likes to ski.

01:54:41.580 --> 01:54:47.440
So the true guardian's curse was immortality.

01:54:47.440 --> 01:54:54.700
And Dr. Capal Smith was the final victim.

01:54:54.700 --> 01:54:59.640
The end.

01:54:59.640 --> 01:55:01.640
See, wasn't that worth letting him borrow it?

01:55:01.640 --> 01:55:03.640
I guess the story was pretty good.

01:55:03.640 --> 01:55:06.640
Hey, the little toe still has my arc.

01:55:06.640 --> 01:56:06.110
Tucker.

01:56:06.110 --> 01:56:08.110
What's up for tonight?

01:56:08.110 --> 01:56:10.110
What nicks nicks again next week?

01:56:10.110 --> 01:56:12.110
It'll be nico-rific.

01:56:12.110 --> 01:56:13.110
Nec-tastic.

01:56:13.110 --> 01:56:15.110
Look at you.

01:56:15.110 --> 01:56:17.110
It'll be...

01:56:17.110 --> 01:56:19.110
So make sure you're here every Saturday night

01:56:19.110 --> 01:56:21.110
when your clock strikes.

01:56:21.110 --> 01:56:22.110
There.

